node.text: BOOKS I READ ON VACATION: 1. Anderson Cooper’s new one, about the rise and fall of the Vanderbilt dynasty, is fascinating - full of intrigue & heart (like him). I loved it.  It’s out in 2 weeks- Pre-order it!  2. HAPPY ALL THE TIME by Laurie Colwin is a timeless story about two couples in love.  It’s a sweet quick read and I dug it!  3. MAYFLIES by Andrew O’Hagan is about friendship, life, and death. The ending had me sobbing like a ninny on the beach. It’s a beautiful book. 4. I couldn’t put THE VANISHING HALF, by Brit Bennett, down. I went into it cold and was gripped til the end, and I’ll leave it at that.  5. I’m almost done with 11 IN 11 by Ben Hochman, a deep dive into the St. Louis Cardinals unreal 2011 season. If you love baseball, this one’s for you. 6. I couldn’t get enough of Richard Scarry as a kid and RICHARD SCARRY’S BUSYTOWN SEEK AND FIND has gotten Ben through the second half of the pandemic. I have limited patience but I’m tickled by the illustrations. Pickle Cars! Pigs!  7. If you’ve gotten this far then you clearly love books (or are bored) and might be interested in pre-ordering my new one, GLITTER EVERY DAY: 365 QUOTES FROM WOMEN I LOVE. Sorry to turn this into a plug but the link is in my bio and I’d be a poor marketer not to mention it!
